mind creating doubled pawns on the 'f' file. The dark-squared bishop is more
important.}) (9. Qd3 {white is ready to play a3 and take on c5 next. However,
this has a clear drawback- the bishop cannot retreat to d3/e2.} Na5 $1 10. dxc5
{white is forced to release the tension which solves all our opening problems.}
(10. Bb5 a6 $17) 10... Bxc5 11. Qxd8 Rxd8 12. Be2 Nc6 13. a3 a6 $11) (9. dxc5 {
This is generally an attempt to simplify the game but there is still enough
