{[%evp 0,42,28,16,23,11,5,5,22,27,23,27,30,18,0,19,14,8,10,8,33,1,65,50,44,39,
39,44,41,29,33,32,34,23,34,28,27,3,16,-6,7,-25,18,-37,4]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3.
Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd3 d5 6. a3 {This has become a very critical and trendy
option in recent times. white forces us to take on c3 but plays a
non-developing move.} Bxc3+ (6... Be7 {does not make much sense here} 7. Nf3
$14) 7. bxc3 dxc4 {We release the tension in the center. If white can get Nf3
and 0-0 comfortably he is just better. We need to act swiftly here.} (7... c5 {
This is a common inaccuracy which I see in many amateur games.} 8. cxd5 exd5 9.
Ne2 $36 {[%cal Ge1g1,Gf2f3,Ge2g3,Ge3e4] This structure is very dangerous for
black as white prepares the move e4 in the center. It can be played with very
good preparation but I prefer to play more sound lines.}) 8. Bxc4 c5 {We are
ahead in development and want to fight back in the center. Our next move is
going to be Qc7 and white is unable to get his ideal piece placement with Bd3
and Nf3. He has a few other options to choose from- Ne2, Bd3/a2 and Nf3, Bd3/
a2. The general rule is to go for the e5 plan when the bishop goes to d3 and
otherwise, we can go for the move b6.} 9. Nf3 {This is the most natural square
for the knight but it also means there is not much danger of a kingside attack
for us. Instead white is trying to make use of his bishop pair and build his
center.} (9. Bb2 Qc7 (9... b5 $5 {is interesting but I do not want to deviate
from our general plan.}) 10. Qe2 (10. Be2 b5 $1 $146 {We make use of the move
Bb2 and gain space on the queenside.} 11. Nf3 Bb7 12. O-O c4 {We completely
restrict the bishop on b2. We will attempt to go for the move e5 soon.} 13. Nd2
Re8 14. Qc2 e5 $11) 10... e5 $1 $146 {There is no need for any preparation
here. We can directly go for the move e5 with the knight still on g1.} 11. dxe5
(11. Nf3 e4 12. Nd2 Bg4 13. f3 Bh5 $11) 11... Qxe5 12. Nf3 Qe7 13. O-O Nc6 14.
Bd3 Bg4 15. c4 Bh5 $11 {We will go Bg6 next and trade the bishops. The
position is pretty even.}) (9. Bd3 Qc7 10. Bb2 {white wants to get his knight
