Qc3+ $19) 10... Nc6 $1 {As per our general rule, we go for the e5 plan when
the bishop is on d3.} 11. Nf3 (11. e4 $6 {is too ambitious with the knight
still on g1.} Qa5 $1 12. Qd2 b6 $1 (12... Rd8 {1/2-1/2 (47) Milov,V (2595)
-Guido,F (2332) Genova 2003}) 13. Ne2 Ba6 14. Bxa6 Qxa6 15. f3 Na5 $15 {
There are a lot of weaknesses for white on the queenside.}) 11... e5 $1 {
The main point in these positions is that white is unable to go for the move d5
