Kxg2 Nf4+ $11 {The position simplifies but black has slightly better chances
in the endgame due to the pawn structures on the kingside.}) 15... h6 16. h5 (
16. Bxf6 {is a terrible move} Qxf6 $17) 16... Ne7 17. Bxf6 gxf6 {We should be
happy to see the doubled pawns as we usually want to keep the game going.} 18.
Re1 f5 $11) 15. d5 {which leads to a lot of simplifications.} exd5 16. Bxd5 (
16. Qd3 d4 $11) 16... Bxd5 17. Bxf6 Qxf6 18. Qxd5 Rad8 $11 {The position is
quite symmetrical and completely equal.} *


