{[%evp 0,52,23,23,24,-11,-6,6,26,30,30,28,28,18,17,25,10,10,26,24,45,30,65,38,
30,19,17,25,25,43,48,25,29,29,26,26,48,39,34,37,28,25,42,41,41,36,27,33,33,29,
24,16,19,8,6] How to continue here?} 10... h6 $1 {We continue with our usual
plan- stop Bg5 and then eventually release the tension in the center.} 11. Bb1
{The rook on a1 is cut off from the game.} (11. Qc2 {does not make much sense}
cxd4 12. Rd1 e5 $15) (11. Re1 Qd7 $1 {We want to get our rook to d8 quickly to
put pressure on d4.} 12. dxc5 (12. Qd3 Rd8 $15 {[%cal Ge6e5]}) 12... Bxc3 13.
bxc3 Qxd1 14. Rxd1 Ne4 {We will win back one of the pawns with a great
position.}) 11... cxd4 12. exd4 Bb6 {We provoke the bishop to e3 and will next
bring the knight to f5.} 13. Be3 Ne7 $11 {[%cal Ge7f5]} *

