{[%evp 0,7,22,16,16,16,-6,25,-7,-3] Which plan to go for?} 10... Nc6 $1 {
As per our general rule, we go for the e5 plan when the bishop is on d3.} 11.
Nf3 (11. e4 $6 {is too ambitious with the knight still on g1.} Qa5 $1 12. Qd2
b6 $1 (12... Rd8 {1/2-1/2 (47) Milov,V (2595) -Guido,F (2332) Genova 2003}) 13.
Ne2 Ba6 14. Bxa6 Qxa6 15. f3 Na5 $15 {There are a lot of weaknesses for white
on the queenside.}) 11... e5 $1 {The main point in these positions is that
white is unable to go for the move d5 due to the bishop on d3. This is why our
e5 plan is so effective here.} 12. dxe5 (12. Qc2 $2 {is a big mistake} cxd4 13.
cxd4 e4 $1 14. Bxe4 Nxe4 15. Qxe4 Qa5+ 16. Nd2 Bf5 $17 {white is in a lot of
trouble with the king stuck in the center for a while.}) 12... Nxe5 13. Nxe5
Qxe5 {white is still not able to castle yet as Ng4 is a big threat.} *


