{[%evp 0,17,-36,2,-20,42,-42,-36,-26,-27,-7,-18,-19,11,11,11,-12,-5,-4,-11]
How to continue here?} 14... Rad8 $1 {There is no need for us to take on d4.
Currently, there is no way for him to go e4 without losing full control over
the center. So we will just continue improving our pieces.} 15. Rb1 a6 {
Getting b5 and c4 on the queenside would be great for us.} 16. h3 {This is a
good sign for us as the g3 knight is now undefended.} (16. Qc2 {runs into} c4
$1 $17) 16... cxd4 $1 {We immediately exploit it and get our knight to d7.} 17.
e4 Nd7 18. Qc2 (18. f5 $4 Qxg3 $19) 18... Rc8 {We are preparing Na5 to get the
queens off the board.} 19. e5 (19. f5 Qxg3 20. Bf4 Qh4 21. fxe6 fxe6 $11) 19...
Ncxe5 20. Bxh7+ Kh8 21. Qxc7 Rxc7 22. Be4 Nc6 $11 {white will probably be able
to win back the pawns but the best he can hope for is equality.} *

