{[%evp 0,11,-22,34,-44,-58,-58,-71,-106,-42,-49,-70,-70,67] How to continue
here?} 15... Nd7 $1 $146 {I like this idea to get our knight to the ideal c5
square.} 16. f4 Nc5 17. Rc1 b6 18. f5 $1 {white's play revolves around the
dark squares and he restricts our light-squared bishop.} Qe7 19. f6 (19. Rxc5
$5 bxc5 20. Qh5 c4 21. f6 gxf6 22. Bxc4 Bb7 $11 {The position is very complex
but dynamically equal.}) 19... Qe5 $1 {We do not weaken our kingside
unnecessarily.} 20. fxg7 Re8 $11 *

