{[%evp 0,11,-16,-5,-5,-13,-27,-9,-5,51,24,8,-15,16] How to continue here?}
10... b5 $1 {Why not take the chance to gain maximum space on the queenside.} (
10... b6 {also possible}) 11. O-O Bb7 12. Qe2 (12. Re1 Nbd7 13. Bb2 Nb6 14. Rc1
{I had a great position in the game 1-0 (73) Korobov,A (2651) -Arjun,K (2516)
Chess.com INT 2023 but I should have continued with-} c4 $1 $17 {We have full
control over e4.}) (12. Bb1 Nbd7 13. Qe2 Ne4 {We do not allow him to get in
the move e4.} 14. Bb2 Bc6 15. Bd3 Rab8 $11) 12... Rc8 {We play a useful
waiting move letting white commit to a plan.} 13. Bb1 {white prepares the move
e4 and as usual we go for the move-} (13. Rd1 Ne4 14. Bb2 c4 {We are always
happy to keep the queenside and the center closed.} 15. Nd2 Nd7 $11) 13... Ne4
$1 {This sacrifices a pawn but black has tremendous compensation with the
bishop on c1.} (13... Nc6 $11) 14. Bb2 (14. Bxe4 Bxe4 15. Qxb5 Nd7 16. Qe2 c4
$44 {I think most players would take black here any day.}) 14... Nd7 15. Rc1 (
15. Qxb5 {1/2-1/2 (31) Santos Latasa,J (2585) -Milliet,S (2398) Sitges 2019} c4
$1 16. Qa4 Rab8 17. Qc2 Ba8 $15 {We will be going f5 next and jumping to b3
with the rook.}) 15... Nd6 $11 {We have very good control over c4 and white
has to be careful to not get worse.} *

