{[%evp 0,11,-6,-15,-16,-32,-8,-14,-11,2,-14,-14,-6,12] How to continue here?}
7... c5 $1 {white has wasted a move with his knight and it is not in contact
with the center. This gives us the ideal opportunity to immediately break in
the center.} 8. cxd5 (8. dxc5 dxc4 9. Qc2 (9. Qxd8 {The exchange of queens
leads to a roughly position but I do prefer the knight on f6 over g3.} Rxd8 10.
Bxc4 Bxc5 $11) (9. Bxc4 Qxd1+ 10. Kxd1 Bxc5 $11) 9... b5 $1 {white is not
going to win back the pawn so easily.} 10. cxb6 Bb7 11. bxa7 Nbd7 $132 {
We have given up two pawns but we aim to go Ne5 next. white has to be pretty
careful here.}) 8... cxd4 {We give white an unpleasant choice- either play
with the IQP or bring your queen out too early and waste some tempi.} 9. exd4 (
9. Qxd4 exd5 {We will follow with Nc6 and d4 soon.}) 9... Nxd5 {[%csl Rg3] The
knight does not belong on g3 in this structure.} 10. Bd3 Nc6 11. O-O Bf6 {
This is the big issue- the f3 pawn is too weak.} 12. Nge2 {A very sad move to
play.} (12. Be3 Nxe3 13. fxe3 g6 $15) 12... Nce7 $11 {[%cal Gc8d7,Gd7c6]} *

