{[%evp 0,15,21,42,33,29,29,56,28,28,-22,2,-34,-34,-32,-40,-29,-19] How to
continue here?} 8... c5 $1 {We want to get the pawn to c4 quickly. This is a
very rare move (5th most popular) but it has been played by a few strong
players. I like the fact that some of the most played moves here actually lead
to a slight edge for us.} 9. a3 {Looks natural but is an inaccuracy as it
allows us to get quick play on the queenside.} (9. Bd3 $6 {Invites us to go c4
which was our plan anyway.} c4 10. Bb1 Bxc3 $1 $146 {This makes a lot of sense
here as we will play differently depending on how white recaptures.} 11. Bxc3 {
This looks more active preparing to go Ne5 next but we stop it with-} (11. bxc3
Nc6 12. O-O Re8 $15 {We can continue with Bg4 and b5 next. white lacks any
counterplay.}) 11... Bg4 $1 {We will either take on f3 or force white to make
weakness on the kingside (with h3,g4) .} 12. h3 (12. O-O b5 $15) 12... Bh5 13.
b3 b5 14. bxc4 bxc4 15. Qa4 Bxf3 16. gxf3 Qc8 $15 {We will go Nc6-e7 next.
With the center closed the bishops lack good diagonals.}) 9... Bxc3 10. Bxc3 c4
$1 {We close down the center and will get our knight to the juicy e4 square
soon. Another plan is to b5, a5 and b4.} 11. b3 (11. Nd2 {is pretty slow.} b5
12. Be2 Nc6 13. b3 Re8 14. O-O Bf5 15. Re1 Qd6 16. bxc4 bxc4 17. Ra1 Rab8 $17 {
1/2-1/2 (70) Navara,D (2684) -Santos Latasa,J (2668) Katowice 2022}) (11. Be2
b5 12. O-O Be6 $15 {[%cal Gb8c6] Here we will try to go Nc6, a5 and b4.}) (11.
Ne5 Ne4 12. Be2 Nxc3 {Again we take on c3 as we want white to decide how to
recapture.} 13. bxc3 (13. Rxc3 b5 $15) 13... Qe7 14. Ra1 Nd7 15. Nxd7 Bxd7 $15)
11... b5 12. bxc4 bxc4 (12... dxc4 $5 $15) 13. Be2 Ne4 14. O-O Bg4 {We would
like to trade the light-squared bishops and play against the bishop on c3.} 15.
h3 Bh5 $15 {0-1 (52) Colovic,A (2449) -Hracek,Z (2578) Skopje 2019} *

