{[%evp 0,15,22,48,28,50,50,106,78,73,52,59,28,35,28,7,22,27] How to continue
here?} 9... c4 $1 {This is quite a commital decision but we believe in our
play on the queenside. We will soon take on c3 and go for b5-b4.} 10. O-O (10.
b3 Bxc3 $1 {We give up our bishop to get the move b5 and maintain our grip on
the queenside.} 11. Bxc3 b5 12. bxc4 bxc4 13. Nd2 {Happened in the game 0-1 (47
) Bluebaum, M (2672) -Lazavik, D (2553) Chess.com INT 2023. We are already
taking over the initiative after-} Bf5 14. f3 (14. O-O Re8 $15 {[%csl Re3]})
14... Nbd7 15. O-O Nb6 $11 {[%csl Ge3][%cal Gf8e8]}) 10... a6 $1 {Now we
prepare b5 without having to take on c3.} 11. Ne5 (11. a3 Bxc3 12. Bxc3 {
In the game 0-1 (53) Sandipan,C (2475) -Panesar, V (2387) New Delhi 2023 black
could have taken over after} (12. bxc3 Qe7 $17) 12... b5 $15 {[%cal Gf6e4]}) (
11. a4 Nc6 12. b3 Bxc3 {We take on c3 whenever white tries to break our
structure on the queenside.} 13. Bxc3 b5 14. Ne5 {Happened in 1/2-1/2 (65)
Aditya,M (2459) -Sethuraman,S (2620) Castelldefels 2021.} Qb6 {A nice
prophylactic move aimed against the move f3.} 15. f3 Nxe5 16. dxe5 Qxe3+ 17.
Kh1 Nh5 $132) 11... b5 12. a4 Qb6 (12... Qd6 $5 {is another option} 13. axb5 (
13. Ra1 Bxc3 14. bxc3 Nc6 $11) 13... Bxc3 14. bxc3 axb5 $11) 13. Ra1 $146 {
This is a very move to play.} (13. Qc2 {0-1 (34) Gupta, A (2628) -Giri, A (2774
) Chess.com INT 2021 CBM 204 Extra [Giri, Anish]} Bxc3 14. bxc3 Nc6 15. Nxc6
Qxc6 $15) 13... Bb7 14. Qc2 Bxc3 15. bxc3 (15. Bxc3 b4 $17) 15... Nc6 16. Nxc6
Bxc6 $11 {We will soon regroup our pieces to the kingside, The queenside is
under control.} *

