{[%evp 0,19,5,9,9,15,20,13,27,58,-4,5,0,15,-15,-7,0,0,0,0,0,0] How to continue
here?} 9... c5 $1 {Why do we need to prepare this? Lets make maximum use of
our lead in development.} 10. dxc5 {white takes our bait.} (10. Be2 {Is quite
slow. The center comes under fire quickly.} cxd4 11. exd4 dxc4 12. bxc4 Nc6 {
We want to go Rc8 and Na5 next.} 13. O-O Rc8 14. Bb2 Ne4 (14... Na5 {is also
fine} 15. Ne5 Ne4 16. Qh3 Ng5 17. Qg4 f6 18. h4 fxe5 19. hxg5 Rf5 20. dxe5 Bxg2
21. Rfd1 Qe7 22. Qxg2 Rxg5 23. Bg4 Rg6 24. Rd6 Nxc4 25. Rxe6 Rxe6 26. Qd5 Rcc6
{1/2-1/2 (26) Turko,S (2383) -Johnson,B (2311) ICCF email 2011}) 15. Qe3 Na5
16. c5 (16. Rac1 Nd6 $11 {[%csl Rc4]}) 16... bxc5 (16... Bd5 $5 {We keep the b2
bishop restricted.} 17. Bd3 f5 $11) 17. dxc5 Bd5 $11 {We are going to win the
pawn on c5 next. white has to prove his compensation. The position is
dynamically balanced.}) 10... Ne4 11. Qc2 Nd7 $1 {Our aim is to keep playing
for the initiative as long as the king is still in the center. We are not too
worried about the material.} 12. cxb6 {This is the most ambitious and greedy
move. We have no intention of recapturing it yet.} (12. Bb2 Rc8 13. cxb6 dxc4
14. Bxc4 Nxb6 15. O-O Bd5 {We win back the pawn with complete equality.} 16.
Rfd1 Qe7 17. Bd4 Nxc4 18. bxc4 Rxc4 19. Qb2 f6 $11 {1/2-1/2 (31) Gong,S (1893)
-Xie,K (2224) Hainan 2023}) 12... dxc4 13. bxc4 {white is okay with damaging
his pawn structure to maintain the pawn.} (13. Bxc4 Nxb6 14. O-O Rc8 $11 {
We will go Bd5 and win the pawn next.}) 13... Ndc5 (13... Nxb6 {is also fine
and we will win the pawn back soon.}) 14. Be2 Qf6 15. Ra2 (15. Bb2 Qg6 16. O-O
Ng3 $17 {We are much better here. I will leave it up to you to figure out the
details.}) 15... axb6 16. O-O Nc3 {We win the light-squared bishop and have
terrific compensation due to the bishop on b7.} 17. Bb2 Nxe2+ 18. Qxe2 Qg6 $44
{The knight on f3 can hardly move anywhere.} *

