{How to continue here?} 10... c5 $1 {As I have mentioned several times our
main aim is to open up the center as quickly as possible. We are often willing
to sacrifice a pawn to open the 'c' file.} 11. dxc5 (11. cxd5 {Here we have a
lot of options. I decided to go with the one which helps us keep winning
chances open.} g5 $5 {This does weaken the kingside but it keeps the queens on
the board.} (11... Nxd5 {leads to an equal endgame.} 12. Bxd8 Nxc3 13. Bxb6
axb6 14. bxc3 Ra5 15. Kd2 Nd7 16. Bd3 Rfa8 17. Ne2 Rxa3 18. Rxa3 Rxa3 $11) (
11... Bxd5 12. Nh3 (12. dxc5 Nbd7) 12... cxd4 13. Qxd4 Nc6 14. Qf4 e5 15. Bxf6
Qxf6 16. Qxf6 gxf6 $11) 12. Bg3 (12. Bf2 {is pretty similar.} Nxd5 13. Qd2 cxd4
$11 {[%cal Gb8c6]}) 12... Nxd5 13. Qd2 Nc6 14. h4 (14. dxc5 Na5 $1 $15 {
We exploit the weakness on the queenside.}) 14... cxd4 15. exd4 Rc8 {We have
brought almost all our pieces into the game.} 16. hxg5 Qxg5 17. Qxg5+ hxg5 $11
{We have pretty good chances to outplay our opponents in this endgame.}) 11...
Nbd7 $1 {In the spirit of our repertoire. We are happy to open as many lines as
possible.} (11... bxc5 {is also possible.}) 12. cxb6 {Again we have a choice
between two recaptures. I think a lot depends on how you feel about these kind
of positions.} (12. cxd5 g5 $1 {We want to take on d5 with the knight.} 13.
dxe6 Nd5 14. Qd2 Nxc5 15. Rd1 gxh4 16. e4 Qf6 $5 {is an option to keep winning
chances alive.} (16... fxe6 {So far all the previous moves were more or less
forced. This should likely lead to a forced draw.} 17. exd5 Qxd5 18. Qxh6 Qe5+
19. Ne2 Rad8 20. Qg6+ Kh8 21. Qh6+ $11) 17. exd5 fxe6 18. d6 Rad8 $44) 12...
axb6 {I like this a bit more as it is easier to understand and the lines are a
bit more forcing.} 13. cxd5 Rc8 14. Qd2 Ne4 $1 {We go for an endgame but our
initiative against the white king continues.} 15. Bxd8 Nxd2 16. dxe6 (16. Kxd2
Rfxd8 17. dxe6 Ne5+ 18. Ke1 fxe6 $44 {The rook is ready to penetrate to the 7th
rank soon.}) 16... Nxf1 17. exd7 Rcxd8 18. Kxf1 Rxd7 {We are two pawns down
here but we have enough compensation due to our activity and the open 'c' and
'd' files.} *

