{[%evp 0,48,25,19,21,4,4,4,28,-6,0,0,11,19,-2,-2,7,-15,-12,-12,3,-1,14,13,13,
13,13,9,2,2,73,2,5,2,-31,-31,5,-12,46,48,30,24,24,20,23,18,37,37,29,29,29] How
to continue here?} 18... Qd2 $1 {We simplify the position even at the cost of
the pawn. We do have the bishop pair.} 19. Bxh7+ (19. Qxd2 Bxd2 $11) 19... Kh8
{The problem for white is that he is not able to preserve the extra pawn. We
have too many threats.} 20. Rfd1 (20. Qe4 Bd6 {Rf4 is a threat now.} 21. Nb5
Rf4 22. Rad1 Nxf3+ $1 23. Qxf3 Bc5+ 24. Kh1 Rxf3 $11 {will lead to a lot of
simplifications.}) 20... Nxf3+ 21. Nxf3 Qe3+ 22. Qf2 Bc5 $1 23. Qxe3 Bxe3+ 24.
Kg2 Kxh7 $11 {The endgame is even but we have the potential to take over with
our bishop pair.} *

